description:
&lt;p&gt;These posts are being advertised to address a temporary need of 12 months however the Trust has made the commitment to offer the successful applicant a permanent contract with the Trust. In the event that the need for this post ends, a suitable alternative post will be offered. Applicants should be aware that alternatives may require some flexibility on role and/or location.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited from applicants who are a Registered Nurse and hold a current registration on the appropriate professional register. We are looking to appoint Nurses who are highly motivated and enthusiastic about working within an award winning CAMHS Crisis, Liaison and intensive home treatment Service, embedding a multi-agency approach to provide an excellent service to children and young people across County Durham and Darlington.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for motivated and enthusiastic Nurses to join our team. This will be an opportunity to contribute to a service which is subject to ongoing development; the successful applicant will be able to develop leadership skills within a progressive and supportive team,.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a very exciting role in a service that has won multiple awards for innovative practice, including a Positive Practice in Mental Health Award and a Nursing Times Award. It has attracted significant national interest due to its success in responding to the huge challenge of emergency mental health care for young people; the team were involved in developing new national guidance for emergency mental health care for young people and have been identified as an area of good practice by the CQC and NHS England. Existing team members are keen to go over and above the norm to provide a creative and proactive approach in engaging young people. It is this culture which has underpinned the success of the team and ensured that what was a project, has now been commissioned as an integral part of the wider CAMHS service. Applicants would be expected to compliment this team culture to contribute to ongoing service development and continued high quality care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To apply for this role, which covers the area of County Durham and Darlington, you will have experience in mental health services and knowledge of child and adolescent mental health. You will also have an understanding of relevant legislation (e.g. Mental Health Act, Mental Capacity Act), detailed understanding of Safeguarding and Clinical Risk Assessment and Management and its application in practice. The ability to make balanced decisions and use positive risk taking approaches, whilst managing potentially high pressure situations is an essential part of this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In exchange you will be well supported, with continuing opportunities for your on-going professional development. As the team continues to develop you will be given the opportunity to influence and contribute to service development, providing a high degree of job satisfaction and personal progression.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job Share will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The interview process will take the form of an interview and short presentation, title to be given on the day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants must ensure that prior to applying they have agreement from their current line manager that they can be released on a secondment basis.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clare Anderson, Team Manager on 08000 516171 or 07920 766316 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;clare.anderson1@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Amy Harrison, Clinical Nurse Specialist on 08000 516171 or 07900 138223 amy.harrison29@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
